<docbook><section><title>WhatDoesShowRemarksDo</title><para> </para><bridgehead class="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml:h2">What does Show Remarks do?</bridgehead>
<para>Show Remarks affects output from the SQLColumns ODBC API call.
 Use this option in conjuntion with Oracle queries.</para><para>When enabled, the REMARKS column of a SQLColumns result set includes the comments from the COMMENTS column of the Oracle ALL_ COL_ COMMENTS data dictionary view.
 When disabled, the REMARKS column is empty.</para><para>Disabling Show Remarks improves performance.
</para></section></docbook>